CODESCHOOL - JQUERY NOTES

What is it?

What can it do?
Clicking makes login dropdown appear, price is update when people select something, styles change when you click a button

Find elements in html
change it
listen to what a user does
animate content
talk over the network to fetch new content.


In our browser, html is organized in the Document Object Model (DOM)
Tree like structure

Browser load html into DOM piece by piece

Document > html > head > title
	>body 	> h1
		>p

jQuery makes it possible for one piece of code to operate with all the modern browsers. Each has a slightly different DOM interface.



